      {
        "id": "09841afb34c03afd652e847ec78b805afc664a21",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 681,
          "name": "Chris Lott",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "cl778h@att.com",
          "username": "cl778h"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-07-19 13:10:13.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis adjusts Jenkins to build and deploy the portal sdk jars from the new repo portal/sdk using file name portal-sdk.yaml.\n\nDoes a new Jenkins job just spring into existence or is there a control file I must also modify?  How do we turn off the old one?  Should I remove the old YAML file entirely?\n\nAlso some questions about the new config file:\n\n1. I modified it to have a settings entry but that does not exist yet - how do I create a settings file?\n\n\tmvn-settings: 'portal-sdk-settings'\n\n2. There have been no releases yet of this one, so I removed these entries\n\n     - 'release-1.0.0':\n         branch: 'release-1.0.0'\n     - 'release-1.1.0':\n         branch: 'release-1.1.0'\n\nPlease help me get this right, thanks in advance.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "8150fb6663aaaac94dfe0330bdac4bdd1b7ee7e0",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 45,
          "name": "Manoop Talasila",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "talasila@research.att.com",
          "username": "talasila"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-07-19 13:56:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "dc4a247d6ceb550389ae7dbcd39872359536e841",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1,
          "name": "Andrew Grimberg",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "agrimberg@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "agrimberg"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-07-19 16:42:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> This adjusts Jenkins to build and deploy the portal sdk jars from\n > the new repo portal/sdk using file name portal-sdk.yaml.\n > \n > Does a new Jenkins job just spring into existence or is there a\n > control file I must also modify?  How do we turn off the old one? \n > Should I remove the old YAML file entirely?\n\nUpon merge of JJB any jobs that do not exist in Jenkins will automatically be created. If a job is removed it will be deleted. If a job is modified then it will be updated.\n\n > Also some questions about the new config file:\n > \n > 1. I modified it to have a settings entry but that does not exist\n > yet - how do I create a settings file?\n > \n > mvn-settings: 'portal-sdk-settings'\n\nThe ${project}-settings files are maintained by LF Release Engineering as they are the publishing credentials into Nexus for the given project.\n\n > 2. There have been no releases yet of this one, so I removed these\n > entries\n > \n > - 'release-1.0.0':\n > branch: 'release-1.0.0'\n > - 'release-1.1.0':\n > branch: 'release-1.1.0'\n\nThat was the correct thing to do.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
